{
  "buggy_files": ["drivers/acpi/video_detect.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["video_detect_dmi_table"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Acer TravelMate 5735Z with board name BA51_MV is missing from the video_detect_dmi_table in kernel 5.6.7. This table contains DMI quirks that specify which backlight driver should be used for specific hardware. Without an entry for this laptop, the automatic backlight selection logic defaults to ACPI video backlight control, which is broken on this device. The fix requires adding a new DMI quirk entry that matches the Acer TravelMate 5735Z and forces the use of native backlight control via the video_detect_force_native callback. The DMI matches should check for sys_vendor='Acer', product_name='TravelMate 5735Z', and board_name='BA51_MV'. This entry was later added to the kernel (as seen in the current torvalds/linux at lines 703-711) to resolve bug #207835."
}

